037-4B06-BC32-5785BE08DBFC</gtr:id><gtr:firstName>Emanuele</gtr:firstName><gtr:surname>Massetti</gtr:surname><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>PRINCIPAL_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role><gtr:role><gtr:name>FELLOW</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/projects?ref=ES%2FG022801%2F1"><gtr:id>F6D2E023-32E6-41B1-9B55-390DF12B1C22</gtr:id><gtr:title>Regionalist Parties' Strategies in Changing Political Environments: A Comparative Analysis of Ideological Development and Adaptation.</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/G022801/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>This research constitutes a direct contribution to the literature on regionalist parties. However, it will be of interest for other adjacent fields, such as multi-level politics, party competition and party system change, the politics of secession and/or constitutional reform, changing understanding of the concept of sovereignty in the context of globalisation and European integration.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>The study represents a fundamental step towards the building of a theory of regionalist parties' positioning in the multi-dimensional ideological space. The empirical material concerns four cases, the Northern League, the South Tyrolese People?s Party, Plaid Cymru&amp;nbsp;- The Party of Wales and the Scottish National Party, to which a new interesting case, the Sicily-centred Movement for Autonomy, is added during the Post-Doctoral Fellowship. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The case studies are compared and contrasted in regard to their positioning along three ideological dimensions: centre-periphery, left-right and European integration. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The research highlights the impact of socio-cultural and socio-economic features of the regions, the type of party system and internal ideological consistency on regionalist parties' positioning. The trends and regularities identified from in depth analysis of the four cases are then tested through cross-tabulations on the 43 most relevant regionalist parties which have been active in seven Western European states since WW2.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;br />&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2010-12-31</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2010-01-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>71444</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications/><gtr:identifiers><gtr:identifier type="RCUK">ES/G022801/1</gtr:identifier></gtr:identifiers><gtr:healthCategories/><gtr:researchActivities/><gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>B57EEFB7-602E-4F5D-92E4-A0C265266249</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Demography &amp; human geography</gtr:text></gtr:researchSubject><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>541CDC75-F361-4961-9EFE-34B2C8ACE947</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>History</gtr:text></gtr:researchSubject><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>5D762B83-597E-4E91-B2F7-04CBB955175C</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Pol. sci. &amp; internat. studies</gtr:text></gtr:researchSu